
            Video
            David Davis on UK economy and trade after Brexit
            There is a "consistent over-estimation" of the impact of the single market on the UK economy, a former Brexit secretary has said.David Davis was addressing the Treasury Forecasts Fact or Fiction event in London, ahead of the government publishing a series of economic forecasts.He said: "The future of the UK economy does not lie with the EU, but with the wider world."
                
                        28 Nov 2018
                    
                
        
